sentences: Mille Clarkes was born in Toronto and moved to Prince Edward Island with her father when she was 11 years old.
Her father is Canadian artist and composer Gerard Luther Clarkes,  they have worked together on Melodies for Max (2013) and Land Feed the Farmer (2015) for the PEI Council of the Arts.

She currently resides in Belfast, Prince Edward Island where she lives with her son.
She returned to her home in Prince Edward Island with 60–70 hours of footage and taught herself Final Cut Pro at the Island Media Arts Cooperative.
Stalking Love (2005) was shown in five film festivals and aired more than 20 times on CBC's documentary channel from 2006 to 2009.
